      "description": "Available is a museum-grade 2005 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six power plant with individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system. This example utilizes the desirable Getrag 420G six-speed manual gearbox, providing tactile engagement and precise gear selection. The chassis is structurally sound with no subframe fatigue, and the suspension maintains factory-spec geometry with fresh bushings and dampers. Performance is anchored by a factory-equipped limited-slip differential and an immaculate cooling system. The exterior retains its original deep luster, while the cockpit is devoid of typical Nappa leather bolster wear, making this a turn-key investment for the discerning purist.",
